The paper deals with scheduling and optimization in an OFDMA system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of cyclic delay diversity (CDD) to enhance channel selectivity is a signal processing technique, which falls under the category of cs.SI (signal processing). The paper also discusses the impact of channel fluctuations on multiuser diversity, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication networks (cs.COM).
